    "body": "I don't think we are going to move forward with the two column\nimplementation right now, as there are too many other things about to\nhappen with the notebook.  But in the long run we will probably look\ninto it.\n\nOn Sat, Dec 31, 2011 at 7:21 AM, Bussonnier Matthias\nreply@reply.github.com\nwrote:\n\n> I made a quick test, [this patch](https://gist.github.com/1544221) seem to almost work :\n> \n>  \\* `In` and  `Out`prompt are not perfectly alligned.\n>  \\* It only modifies `notebook.css`, Input grows if typed code is to wide, and horizontal scroll bar appears for to wide output.\n> Markdown cell still take 100% of the width.\n>  \\* Firefox don't take the `min-width` or `width`of input cell into account, which make things not well alligned\n>  \\* This doen't make things configurable.\n> \n> @Tillsten, it is enough for you as a quick fix ? C'ant figure out what goes wrong in firefox, yet it is still a two \"column\" view...\n> With the width in pixel it works with FF , but then I let you choose depending on your monitor resolution.\n> \n> ---\n> \n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub:\n> https://github.com/ipython/ipython/issues/1214#issuecomment-3321497\n\n## \n\nBrian E. Granger\nCal Poly State University, San Luis Obispo\nbgranger@calpoly.edu and ellisonbg@gmail.com\n"
  },
